'''Gustavo Adolfo Puerta Molano''' (born 23 July 2003) is a Colombian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Segunda División]] club [[Racing de Santander]] and the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]].

==Club career==
===Beginnings===
Born in [[La Victoria, Valle del Cauca]], Puerta started playing football at the Talentos Gustavo Victoria Deportes school in [[Tuluá]].<ref name=ep>{{cite web|url=https://www.elpais.com.co/deportes/seleccion-colombia/ejemplo-de-superacion-gustavo-puerta-el-gordito-al-que-no-le-creian-en-el-futbol.html|title=Ejemplo de superación: Gustavo Puerta, el 'gordito' al que no le creían en el fútbol|trans-title=Example of overcoming: Gustavo Puerta, the 'chubby boy' who did not believe in football|first=César|last=Polanía|date=28 January 2023|accessdate=3 February 2023|website=elpais.com.co|language=Spanish}}</ref> He also played for amateur side Supercampeones between the ages of ten and sixteen.<ref name=ep/>

Initially rejected by Colombian [[Categoría Primera A]] side [[Independiente Santa Fe]] in 2019 after a trial, Puerta went on to join [[Categoría Primera B]] side [[Bogotá F.C.|Bogotá]] in 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eldeportivo.com.co/futbol-colombiano/santa-fe/gustavo-puerta-fue-rechazado-por-independiente-santa-fe/|title=Gustavo Puerta fue rechazado por Independiente Santa Fe|trans-title=Gustavo Puerta was rejected by Independiente Santa Fe|date=1 February 2023|accessdate=3 February 2023|website=eldeportivo.com|language=Spanish}}</ref>

===Bayer Leverkusen===
On 31 January 2023, Puerta moved to [[Bundesliga]] side [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]], before immediately being loaned to [[1. FC Nürnberg]] in the [[2. Bundesliga]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/news/bayer04/bayer-04-sign-top-colombian-talent-puerta-loan-deal-with-nuernberg|title=Bayer 04 sign top Colombian talent Puerta – loan deal with Nürnberg|date=31 January 2023|accessdate=3 February 2023|website=bayer04.de}}</ref>

He won the [[2023–24 Bundesliga]] with Bayer Leverkusen.<ref name="bundesliga202324">{{Cite web |date=15 April 2024 |title=Bayer Leverkusen are 2023/24 Bundesliga champions! |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayer-leverkusen-are-2023-24-bundesliga-champions-26930 |accessdate=15 April 2024 |website= |publisher=[[Bundesliga]] |language=en}}</ref>

====Loan to Hull City====
On 27 August 2024, Puerta signed for [[EFL Championship]] side [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]] on a season-long loan, with the club holding an option to buy in the summer of 2025.<ref name="Hull">{{cite news|url=https://www.wearehullcity.co.uk/news/2024/august/27/hull-city-complete-puerta-loan-deal/|title=Hull City complete Puerta loan deal|date=27 August 2024|publisher=Hull City A.F.C.|accessdate=27 August 2024}}</ref> He made his debut on 20 October 2024, in the 0–1 home loss to [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]].<ref>{{cite news
| url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c0qzx7p9ljkt#LiveReporting | title = Hull City Sunderland| date = 20 October 2024| work = BBC Sport | accessdate = 20 October 2024}}</ref> On 12 January 2025, he scored his first goal for the Tigers in an [[2024–25 FA Cup#Third round|FA Cup third round]] tie at home to [[Doncaster Rovers F.C.|Doncaster Rovers]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c3wegv33qzwt|title=Hull City 1–1 Doncaster Rovers|work=[[BBC Sport]]|date=12 January 2025|accessdate=19 April 2025}}</ref>

Two months later, on 12 March 2025, Puerta scored his side's winner in their 2–1 victory over [[Oxford United F.C.|Oxford United]], coincidentally his first league goal for Hull.<ref name="Oxford">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c8x4rg7wp25t|title=Hull City 2–1 Oxford United|work=[[BBC Sport]]|date=12 March 2025|accessdate=19 April 2025}}</ref> In the same match, moments before full-time, the Colombian received his second [[Fouls and misconduct (association football)#Yellow card (caution)|yellow card]] of the game for [[Diving (association football)|diving]], which saw him [[Fouls and misconduct (association football)#Red card (dismissal)|sent off]].<ref name="Oxford"/>

On 19 April 2025, Hull announced that Puerta had activated a clause in his contract that would see him join the Tigers on a permanent basis from 1 July 2025.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.wearehullcity.co.uk/news/2025/april/19/puerta-clause-activated/|title=Puerta Clause Activated|work=[[Hull City A.F.C.]]|date=19 April 2025|accessdate=19 April 2025}}</ref> Although he was initially meant to join Hull City, he was unable to join due to a transfer ban on the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sportwitness.co.uk/hull-city-move-blocked-by-transfer-ban-midfielder-heads-back-to-club/|title=Hull City move blocked by transfer ban – Midfielder heads back to club|first=Pedro|last=Reinert|website=sportwitness.co.uk}}</ref>

===Racing Santander===
On 1 September 2025, [[Racing de Santander]] announced the signing of Puerta on a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realracingclub.es/noticias/el-centrocampista-colombiano-gustavo-puerta-refuerza-la-plantilla-del-racing-202526|title=El centrocampista colombiano Gustavo Puerta refuerza la plantilla del Racing 2025/26|trans-title=Colombian central midfielder Gustavo Puerta bolsters the squad of Racing 2025/26|publisher=Racing Santander|language=es|date=1 September 2025|accessdate=2 September 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Puerta has represented Colombia at under-20 level.<ref name=wf/> Serving as captain of the side he led it to third place at the [[2023 South American U-20 Championship]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Burkhardt |first1=Dirk |title=Gustavo Puerta spielt sich bei Bayer 04 Leverkusen ins Rampenlicht |trans-title=Gustavo Puerta plays his way into the limelight at Bayer 04 Leverkusen |url=https://www1.wdr.de/sport/fussball/erste-bundesliga/puerta-leverkusens-neuer-joker-100.html |accessdate=16 April 2024 |work=WDR |date=2 August 2023 |language=German}}</ref> He was first called up to the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]] for a set of friendlies in November 2025, and scored on his debut in a 2–1 win over [[New Zealand men's national football team|New Zealand]] on 15 November 2025.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/360871048/all-whites-concede-late-winner-against-colombia-florida|title=Stuff|website=www.stuff.co.nz|accessdate=16 November 2025}}</ref>

